column5: Well, being the facebook creeper I am, I came across this picture that someone took of a fish. I look at it, and the head screams Pike, and it also looks like there are very distinctive circles on its side, but I am not 100% and it's hard to tell as I was not there. Now, I beleive these pictures were taken at Ken Reid park, meaning the water is Sturgeon Lake waters, very close to the Scugog River.
looks like a pike to me
platypus.  For some reason I'd bet on pike but its so hard to tell.  Saw this the other day http://muskie.outdoo...tch.asp?id=2282

Really hard to say for sure but there isn't really anything that would make me think it's a pike moreso than a musky. On the other hand, both the body of water and the forked, pointed tail side with musky.  I'm going with musky.  Edit: Also, I've seen numerous musky sitting like that in flowing water, especially during the spring.
It looks kinda beat up, making it harder to tell.. Just found out it was in Ken Reid for sure.
I'm going with musky....sides look pretty light, looks like dark pattern on lighter body....I've seen quite a few muskies sunning themselves like that, not so much with pike
Ya I've seen many Musky sunning in the river like that.

not enough contrast on the sides. I think the light spots on the dark sides of a pike would be more visible if that was a pike. I have caught muskies that have very little markings so here's a vote for musky. To me, pike always look pretty much the same (except those blue or albino freaks)but muskies can have a broad range of appearance from striped to spotted to green to silver...
Cool video of the fish in the current, my vote is Muskie for the photo Ryan.
musky.
I still see a Pike head when I look at it.. And ya, that video is siiiick, huge fish. I see now that what I though were marking is the sun shining on its side, lol.   Looks like a young fish
I swear people on this board are blind.....Atlantic  -Ben
I remember that thread, went to check it after a bit and it totally vanished
tail looks forked to me... although it's hard to tell, my money is still on musky.
Hard to tell but the colour of the body seems to be to dark to be a muskie, Im goin with pike
Come on guys - admit it - the pic isn't good enough to be able to tell.
there has been a few pike caught out of scoug the last couple years and the ministry has then for research.  good chance it is a pike as they could work there way through the trent sevren....
Carp
Grabbed my Bluewater Optics & no more glare so Pike it is maybe:dunno: Richard
Looks like a long, slender fish built for speed.
Let's call it a Tiger Musky and keep everyone Happy.   Clarence
Burbot

I'd say its a musky.  Judging by where it was taken, I sure as hell hope it is a musky, and not a pike. I've spent a lot of years on sturgeon, and never seen or heard of one out of there YET. You never know I guess....  S.
Tiller.
